In [3]:
def get_ccsuid(x):
    try:
        y = x[-7::]
    except:
        y = np.nan
    return y

In [49]:
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,4))

dfAgg = df.groupby(['Technologies', 'UOM']).agg({'VALUE':'sum'}).sort_values(by='VALUE', ascending=False)
dfAgg = dfAgg.unstack()
dfAgg.columns = dfAgg.columns.droplevel()
dfAgg = dfAgg.sort_values(by='Number', ascending=True)

dfAgg.plot(ax=ax, kind='barh', legend=None, width=1)

ax.set_ylabel('')
ax.set_xlabel('Number of farms')

ax.set_title('Technologies used on the farm')

In [54]:
dgfGIS = dgf[dgf.Technologies=='GPS technology']
dgfGIS = dgfGIS[~dgfGIS.VALUE.isnull()]
dgfGIS = dgfGIS[~(dgfGIS.VALUE==0)]
dgfGIS['NperKm2'] = dgfGIS.VALUE/dgfGIS.area

f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16,16))

pf.plot(ax=ax, color='white', edgecolor='grey')
dgfGIS.plot(column='NperKm2', ax=ax, legend=False, linewidth=0.1, edgecolor='#dddddd')

plt.axis('off')

ax.set_title('Farms using GPS (# of farms per square kilometer)')
